social_posts.post_text: This means everything to me. Thank you New York. You’re my Athena … you’re the reason I’m still here 🤍

it feels like all we do in life is dodge curveballs. after i lost my grandpa last week, all i can think about is what’s actually important to me … what actually matters in my life? 

my grandpa had been so proud of everything i had accomplished in music (hell he kept one of my plaques in his kitchen). that was important. my niece & nephew are important. the people i am blessed to make art with are important. the stories i tell are important. connection is important, but so also is privacy & stillness. 

im not perfect, never will be, and won’t ever try to be. neither are you, nor is anyone. but we keep going for the beauty of it all. and it is beautiful, i promise. people die, but the love doesn’t have to.

THE PALLADIUM TOUR // CHINA, JULY 2023
Tickets on-sale Thursday, May 18th local Chinese time. 

…

It’s been 4 years since I last was in China. We have been working tirelessly behind-the-scenes to get this tour off the ground; many days, it seemed as if it was going to be impossible. But the light shined through!! I cannot wait to be back with my friends, both old and new, singing Palladium. This is a dream come true. See you in July ❤️
@greysonchance guides us through the making of his latest album “Palladium” in #BehindThePen ✍️

Palladium Lives On .. The Reimagined Edition, featuring @thisismokita @slenderbodies and Slater, Out Now 🤍

My endless thanks & gratitude to these three for creating their versions & bringing my world out in the open, and into color. I never gave up on this album, and it’s not giving up on me. As always, listen loud.

i played Palladium for the first time in June 2022 — that’s over a year of shows across a few continents, and an endless amount of color added into my life. thank you for being on this road with me … i know that im never alone, and for that, im forever grateful

im devoting the rest of my year to finishing a new album. i must have skated 100 miles this summer, at the lake down the street from my mom’s old house, searching for answers, clues of some sort, a roadmap. this is a record about my family, the good, the bad, and all the ugly details in-between. the process is either my way of coping, or perhaps my way of running away from something. im gonna let the music give me that answer.
extra!! extra!!! summer’s over :’)

one year ago today, i released my album Palladium <3  this was my redemption record … to show myself that i was good enough to still be here writing music & creating art … im forever indebted to @jasonreeves for making it with me, and im forever indebted to you all for listening.
Album No. 5 Loading … makes the Heartland boy in me swoon that all the pianos for this album were recorded in Oklahoma

last october, i was a handful of shows into the north america leg of the Palladium Tour .. behind-the-scenes though, i was a bit of a nightmare. my health was shit and it was the most anxious i had ever felt on the road; touring is not for the lighthearted — the thing that got me through though, were those 90 minutes every night when i got to play the show and i got to meet your eyes in the crowd. you all gave me my purpose & strength throughout those two and a half months, and i feel much stronger and much more aware of myself after the fact. so … all to say … thank you for buying a ticket, and thank you for always keeping my head up <3
october still feels too hot

i was so wildly [and blindly] confident when i was making portraits … that’s the beauty of being 20; you think you’re the shit, and no one can tell you otherwise. i’ve been seeing glimpses of that kid in the mirror lately. next year will be an important year for me 🤍
was told over & over that shut up was “good” but that it shouldn’t be a first single .. flash forward and it’s about to cross 100million streams 🤍

shut up is my first song to ever reach 100 million streams !!! thank YOU for streaming and loving my baby which all came from a ten second airport voice memo after a sneaky hookup .. i truly can’t believe 100,000,000 !!!!
